[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":607},["ShallowReactive",2],{"article-/articles/new-test-article-7":3},{"id":4,"title":5,"body":6,"createdAt":593,"description":594,"extension":595,"meta":596,"navigation":334,"path":597,"readingTime":598,"seo":599,"stem":600,"tags":601,"__hash__":606},"articles/articles/new-test-article-7.md","A Guide to Python Virtual Environments",{"type":7,"value":8,"toc":575},"minimark",[9,14,18,22,51,55,63,68,71,100,113,117,120,171,178,182,187,205,208,212,215,224,227,234,237,241,247,266,272,278,294,298,301,466,470,565,568,571],[10,11,13],"h2",{"id":12},"python-virtual-environments-isolation-for-your-projects","Python Virtual Environments: Isolation for Your Projects",[15,16,17],"p",{},"When working on Python projects, you'll often encounter situations where different projects require different versions of libraries, or even different versions of Python itself. This is where Python virtual environments come in handy. A virtual environment is a self-contained directory tree that contains a Python installation for a particular version of Python, plus a number of additional packages.",[10,19,21],{"id":20},"why-use-virtual-environments","Why Use Virtual Environments?",[23,24,25,33,39,45],"ul",{},[26,27,28,32],"li",{},[29,30,31],"strong",{},"Dependency Isolation",": Each project can have its own set of dependencies without affecting other projects or the global Python installation.",[26,34,35,38],{},[29,36,37],{},"Avoid Conflicts",": Prevents \"dependency hell\" where one project's requirements clash with another's.",[26,40,41,44],{},[29,42,43],{},"Clean Project Management",": Keeps project dependencies organized and separate from your system-wide Python packages.",[26,46,47,50],{},[29,48,49],{},"Reproducibility",": Makes it easy to reproduce the exact environment for a project on another machine.",[10,52,54],{"id":53},"how-to-create-and-use-virtual-environments","How to Create and Use Virtual Environments",[15,56,57,58,62],{},"The most common way to create virtual environments in modern Python is using the built-in ",[59,60,61],"code",{},"venv"," module.",[64,65,67],"h3",{"id":66},"_1-create-a-virtual-environment","1. Create a Virtual Environment",[15,69,70],{},"Navigate to your project directory and run:",[72,73,78],"pre",{"className":74,"code":75,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark","python -m venv venv\n","bash","",[59,79,80],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,82,85,89,93,97],"span",{"class":83,"line":84},"line",1,[81,86,88],{"class":87},"svObZ","python",[81,90,92],{"class":91},"sDLfK"," -m",[81,94,96],{"class":95},"sU2Wk"," venv",[81,98,99],{"class":95}," venv\n",[15,101,102,103,105,106,108,109,112],{},"This command creates a directory named ",[59,104,61],{}," (you can choose any name, but ",[59,107,61],{}," is conventional) inside your project, containing the Python executable and ",[59,110,111],{},"pip",".",[64,114,116],{"id":115},"_2-activate-the-virtual-environment","2. Activate the Virtual Environment",[15,118,119],{},"Before installing packages, you need to activate the virtual environment.",[23,121,122,153],{},[26,123,124,127,128],{},[29,125,126],{},"On Windows",":",[72,129,131],{"className":74,"code":130,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},".\\venv\\Scripts\\activate\n",[59,132,133],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,134,135,137,141,143,145,148,150],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,136,112],{"class":91},[81,138,140],{"class":139},"s95oV","\\",[81,142,61],{"class":95},[81,144,140],{"class":139},[81,146,147],{"class":95},"Scripts",[81,149,140],{"class":139},[81,151,152],{"class":95},"activate\n",[26,154,155,127,158],{},[29,156,157],{},"On macOS/Linux",[72,159,161],{"className":74,"code":160,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"source venv/bin/activate\n",[59,162,163],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,164,165,168],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,166,167],{"class":91},"source",[81,169,170],{"class":95}," venv/bin/activate\n",[15,172,173,174,177],{},"Once activated, your terminal prompt will typically change to indicate that you are inside the virtual environment (e.g., ",[59,175,176],{},"(venv) your_username@your_machine:~/your_project$",").",[64,179,181],{"id":180},"_3-install-packages","3. Install Packages",[15,183,184,185,112],{},"With the environment activated, you can now install project-specific packages using ",[59,186,111],{},[72,188,190],{"className":74,"code":189,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"pip install requests beautifulsoup4\n",[59,191,192],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,193,194,196,199,202],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,195,111],{"class":87},[81,197,198],{"class":95}," install",[81,200,201],{"class":95}," requests",[81,203,204],{"class":95}," beautifulsoup4\n",[15,206,207],{},"These packages will be installed only within this virtual environment.",[64,209,211],{"id":210},"_4-deactivate-the-virtual-environment","4. Deactivate the Virtual Environment",[15,213,214],{},"When you're done working on the project, you can deactivate the environment:",[72,216,218],{"className":74,"code":217,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"deactivate\n",[59,219,220],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,221,222],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,223,217],{"class":87},[15,225,226],{},"Your terminal prompt will return to its normal state.",[10,228,230,231],{"id":229},"managing-dependencies-with-requirementstxt","Managing Dependencies with ",[59,232,233],{},"requirements.txt",[15,235,236],{},"It's good practice to keep track of your project's dependencies.",[64,238,240],{"id":239},"exporting-dependencies","Exporting Dependencies",[15,242,243,244,246],{},"To export a list of all installed packages and their versions to a ",[59,245,233],{}," file:",[72,248,250],{"className":74,"code":249,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"pip freeze > requirements.txt\n",[59,251,252],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,253,254,256,259,263],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,255,111],{"class":87},[81,257,258],{"class":95}," freeze",[81,260,262],{"class":261},"snl16"," >",[81,264,265],{"class":95}," requirements.txt\n",[64,267,269,270],{"id":268},"installing-dependencies-from-requirementstxt","Installing Dependencies from ",[59,271,233],{},[15,273,274,275,277],{},"To install all dependencies listed in a ",[59,276,233],{}," file (e.g., when setting up a project on a new machine):",[72,279,281],{"className":74,"code":280,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"pip install -r requirements.txt\n",[59,282,283],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,284,285,287,289,292],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,286,111],{"class":87},[81,288,198],{"class":95},[81,290,291],{"class":91}," -r",[81,293,265],{"class":95},[10,295,297],{"id":296},"example-workflow","Example Workflow",[15,299,300],{},"Let's say you're starting a new web scraping project:",[72,302,304],{"className":74,"code":303,"language":76,"meta":77,"style":77},"# 1. Create project directory\nmkdir my_scraper\ncd my_scraper\n\n# 2. Create virtual environment\npython -m venv venv\n\n# 3. Activate environment\n# On Windows:\n# .\\venv\\Scripts\\activate\n# On macOS/Linux:\nsource venv/bin/activate\n\n# 4. Install necessary packages\npip install requests beautifulsoup4\n\n# 5. Write your Python code (e.g., scraper.py)\n# ... code that uses requests and beautifulsoup4 ...\n\n# 6. Save dependencies\npip freeze > requirements.txt\n\n# 7. Deactivate environment\ndeactivate\n",[59,305,306,312,321,329,336,342,353,358,364,370,376,382,389,394,400,411,416,422,428,433,439,450,455,461],{"__ignoreMap":77},[81,307,308],{"class":83,"line":84},[81,309,311],{"class":310},"sAwPA","# 1. Create project directory\n",[81,313,315,318],{"class":83,"line":314},2,[81,316,317],{"class":87},"mkdir",[81,319,320],{"class":95}," my_scraper\n",[81,322,324,327],{"class":83,"line":323},3,[81,325,326],{"class":91},"cd",[81,328,320],{"class":95},[81,330,332],{"class":83,"line":331},4,[81,333,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},true,"\n",[81,337,339],{"class":83,"line":338},5,[81,340,341],{"class":310},"# 2. Create virtual environment\n",[81,343,345,347,349,351],{"class":83,"line":344},6,[81,346,88],{"class":87},[81,348,92],{"class":91},[81,350,96],{"class":95},[81,352,99],{"class":95},[81,354,356],{"class":83,"line":355},7,[81,357,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},[81,359,361],{"class":83,"line":360},8,[81,362,363],{"class":310},"# 3. Activate environment\n",[81,365,367],{"class":83,"line":366},9,[81,368,369],{"class":310},"# On Windows:\n",[81,371,373],{"class":83,"line":372},10,[81,374,375],{"class":310},"# .\\venv\\Scripts\\activate\n",[81,377,379],{"class":83,"line":378},11,[81,380,381],{"class":310},"# On macOS/Linux:\n",[81,383,385,387],{"class":83,"line":384},12,[81,386,167],{"class":91},[81,388,170],{"class":95},[81,390,392],{"class":83,"line":391},13,[81,393,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},[81,395,397],{"class":83,"line":396},14,[81,398,399],{"class":310},"# 4. Install necessary packages\n",[81,401,403,405,407,409],{"class":83,"line":402},15,[81,404,111],{"class":87},[81,406,198],{"class":95},[81,408,201],{"class":95},[81,410,204],{"class":95},[81,412,414],{"class":83,"line":413},16,[81,415,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},[81,417,419],{"class":83,"line":418},17,[81,420,421],{"class":310},"# 5. Write your Python code (e.g., scraper.py)\n",[81,423,425],{"class":83,"line":424},18,[81,426,427],{"class":310},"# ... code that uses requests and beautifulsoup4 ...\n",[81,429,431],{"class":83,"line":430},19,[81,432,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},[81,434,436],{"class":83,"line":435},20,[81,437,438],{"class":310},"# 6. Save dependencies\n",[81,440,442,444,446,448],{"class":83,"line":441},21,[81,443,111],{"class":87},[81,445,258],{"class":95},[81,447,262],{"class":261},[81,449,265],{"class":95},[81,451,453],{"class":83,"line":452},22,[81,454,335],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":334},[81,456,458],{"class":83,"line":457},23,[81,459,460],{"class":310},"# 7. Deactivate environment\n",[81,462,464],{"class":83,"line":463},24,[81,465,217],{"class":87},[10,467,469],{"id":468},"virtual-environment-commands-summary","Virtual Environment Commands Summary",[471,472,473,490],"table",{},[474,475,476],"thead",{},[477,478,479,484,487],"tr",{},[480,481,483],"th",{"align":482},"left","Action",[480,485,486],{"align":482},"Windows Command",[480,488,489],{"align":482},"macOS/Linux Command",[491,492,493,508,523,537,551],"tbody",{},[477,494,495,499,504],{},[496,497,498],"td",{"align":482},"Create venv",[496,500,501],{"align":482},[59,502,503],{},"python -m venv venv",[496,505,506],{"align":482},[59,507,503],{},[477,509,510,513,518],{},[496,511,512],{"align":482},"Activate venv",[496,514,515],{"align":482},[59,516,517],{},".\\venv\\Scripts\\activate",[496,519,520],{"align":482},[59,521,522],{},"source venv/bin/activate",[477,524,525,528,533],{},[496,526,527],{"align":482},"Deactivate venv",[496,529,530],{"align":482},[59,531,532],{},"deactivate",[496,534,535],{"align":482},[59,536,532],{},[477,538,539,542,547],{},[496,540,541],{"align":482},"Install packages",[496,543,544],{"align":482},[59,545,546],{},"pip install \u003Cpackage>",[496,548,549],{"align":482},[59,550,546],{},[477,552,553,556,561],{},[496,554,555],{"align":482},"Export dependencies",[496,557,558],{"align":482},[59,559,560],{},"pip freeze > req.txt",[496,562,563],{"align":482},[59,564,560],{},[566,567],"hr",{},[15,569,570],{},"Virtual environments are a fundamental tool for any Python developer. They provide a clean, isolated, and reproducible way to manage your project's dependencies, making development smoother and more reliable.",[572,573,574],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .svObZ, html code.shiki .svObZ{--shiki-default:#B392F0}html pre.shiki code .sDLfK, html code.shiki .sDLfK{--shiki-default:#79B8FF}html pre.shiki code .sU2Wk, html code.shiki .sU2Wk{--shiki-default:#9ECBFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .s95oV, html code.shiki .s95oV{--shiki-default:#E1E4E8}html pre.shiki code .snl16, html code.shiki .snl16{--shiki-default:#F97583}html pre.shiki code .sAwPA, html code.shiki .sAwPA{--shiki-default:#6A737D}",{"title":77,"searchDepth":314,"depth":314,"links":576},[577,578,579,585,591,592],{"id":12,"depth":314,"text":13},{"id":20,"depth":314,"text":21},{"id":53,"depth":314,"text":54,"children":580},[581,582,583,584],{"id":66,"depth":323,"text":67},{"id":115,"depth":323,"text":116},{"id":180,"depth":323,"text":181},{"id":210,"depth":323,"text":211},{"id":229,"depth":314,"text":586,"children":587},"Managing Dependencies with requirements.txt",[588,589],{"id":239,"depth":323,"text":240},{"id":268,"depth":323,"text":590},"Installing Dependencies from requirements.txt",{"id":296,"depth":314,"text":297},{"id":468,"depth":314,"text":469},"2022-07-10","Understand why and how to use Python virtual environments to manage project dependencies and avoid conflicts.","md",{},"/articles/new-test-article-7",null,{"title":5,"description":594},"articles/new-test-article-7",[88,602,603,604,605],"development","environments","best-practices","tutorial","8tTRx0wXcQO1_1-Qmg86pCTmGzzP_ON37nZEZCAQwFM",1773168135332]